@node Main "X_Q - Documentation"

                               'X_Q' 1.12

                           by Charles-N. Jacob

  'X_Q' is an 'X' shaped @{" game " link play} like 'Solo' or 'Hi-Q'. You play by jumping
a peg to an empty space either horizontally or diagonally, and depending
if you play the @{" Normal " link play} or @{" Inverted " link play} game, that peg must go over another
peg (or empty space in the Inverted game). In the @{" Normal " link play} game, the
intermediate peg (the one that was jumped over) will be removed. In the
@{" Inverted " link play} game, the intermediate empty space will be replaced by a peg.

  The goal is to remove all the pegs, leaving only one on the board.
If you play the @{" Inverted " link play} game, you start with one peg and you try
to fill the board leaving only one empty space.

  Have fun!

