@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place 'X_Q' where you want on
your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or Libraries
are needed.

                             How to play?

  To move a peg (space with a black and white circle), just click on it
with the mouse pointer and you click on the empty space (space with a
small dot) where you want to move the peg. You can only move a peg 2
spaces horizontally or diagonally. If the move is possible, the selected
peg will go there.

  In 'X_Q' there are two ways to play:

  -The @{b}Normal@{ub} game:   You jump over a @{b}peg@{ub} and that peg will be removed.
                      Try to remove all the pegs until only one is left,
                      preferably where the empty space was located at
                      the start.

  -The @{b}Inverted@{ub} play: You jump over an @{b}empty space@{ub} and a peg will appear
                      there, just as if you would play the normal game
                      backward. Try to 'fill' up the board until only
                      one empty space is left, preferably where the peg
                      was located at the start.

  When there are no possible moves, the game ends and X_Q displays how
many pegs (or free spaces for the 'Inverted' game) are remaining.

OPTIONS

 -@{b}New Game@{ub}:             Restarts the game.

 -@{b}About...@{ub}:             Displays the informations about the game.

 -@{b}Normal/Inverted Game@{ub}: Toggles between the 'Normal' and the 'Inverted' game.

